   The platform for environmental innovation

   Pollutec is established as the reference event for environment
   professionals. It is also a platform for environmental and energy
   solutions for industries, cities and territories, and a springboard for
   innovations and international development.

   Find out more about the exhibition areas:

   Waste    Water     Energy     Air, Odours, Noise     Instrumentation,
   Metrology, Analysis

   Risks Management    Sustainable City    Sites & Soils    Biodiversity
     Institutions & Collectives
   2200 Exhibitors
   400 Conferences
   70000 Professionals
   128 Countries

They're exhibiting in 2020

   Pollutec exhibitors

   See the full list

2018 Show Report

   IFRAME: https://www.youtube.com/embed/LZv_NrP2aaU

   In 2018, Pollutec celebrated its 40th anniversary. With Burkina Faso as
   Country of the Year and a third of international exhibitors, the show
   was a complete success as the meeting place for green growth
   stakeholders.
   Download the report

“Pollutec 2018 was an excellent edition to us: a lot of visitor traffic,
internationals, officials and ministries, but also companies that were
extremely satisfied with the contacts they generated and the quality of the
visitors.”

   Olivier Chazal
   Club ADEME International Manager

“Pollutec is first and foremost a medium to gain visibility, which is vital
for a startup. It is also an incredible concentration of suppliers. Every
person we wished to see, we met at the show. We were at Vivatech, but
Pollutec is an even more important event.”

   Didier Pierrat-Agostini
   CEO, STEPSOL

“The fact that Pollutec is an international event is important to us because
Bouygues is active in over 80 countries. The outcome of Pollutec is that we
were able to present to a large audience our vision of the sustainable city
and the circular economy in the construction sector.”

   Charles Henri Burgelin
   Director of communications Brand and Sustainable Development, Bouygues

“We came to Lyon from Bondy, to meet the Change and Environment stakeholders.
We brought our startups with us, and were able to make a large number of
contacts. We also had the opportunity to hold a conference to develop
awareness on environmental challenges faced by the African continent.”

   Fatimatou Ousmanou
   Incubation Project Manager, Bond'Innov

